  "texts": [
    "Most works focus on fine-tuning the recognition models trained on one dataset to new datasets using transfer learning.",
    "While the transfer learning reduces the amount of manual labeling needed for new datasets, it does not fully solve the problem of multiple domains.",
    "Labeled training data are still needed for all datasets, and the recognition models need to be fine-tuned for each, requiring expertise in machine learning and computing resources.",
    "A more general model can be obtained by using ensemble learning with submodels learned on different datasets if labeled training data on each dataset (imaging instrument) is available.",
    "More sophisticated approaches to plankton image domain adaptation include the capsule neural networks and meta-learning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}